"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmy1665702874862.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmy1665702874862.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmy1665702874862.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533092\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533092\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vmy1665702874862.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vmy1665702874862.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vmy1665702874862.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vmy1665702874862\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Unicode Compatibility Issues\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Earlier versions of Uniface used the Uniface meta character set as its internal character set. Uniface 9 uses Unicode as its internal character set. For compatibility reasons, the meta character set is still used, but this results in some problems. Assignment settings are available to solve these issues.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__section_fgd_fpb_rcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d713055e51\">Missing Characters in Unicode</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__p_d28325e1_d28326e1_d28327e1\">Some characters exist in meta character sets but not in\n        Unicode.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Uniface Meta Characters Missing in Unicode</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Meta Character Code </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,46 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript right arrow </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,47 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript slash </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,58 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript infinity </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,59 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript pi </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,60 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript left angle </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,62 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript right angle </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font2,63 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Superscript delta </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font3,93 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Greenlandic capital K </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__1\">Font7,46 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2921e1_d2922e1_d2923e1__entry__2\">Bottle<a href=\"#fntarg_1\" name=\"fnsrc_1\"><sup>1</sup></a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__p_d28328e1_d28329e1_d28330e1\">Characters in Font 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 7 are shared for all\n        the installable character sets. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aud1665702670477.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1665702670477.html\" title=\"Meta character sets are used for translating installable character sets and defining translation tables. In earlier versions of Uniface, meta character sets were used as internal character sets instead of Unicode.\">Meta Character Sets</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__section_x5t_jpb_rcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d713055e183\">Incorrectly Returned Mappings</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__p_d28334e1_d28335e1_d28336e1\">Some characters have two entry points in the meta\n        character set. For example, symbol ± appears in Font1,49 and Font7,93. However, in Unicode,\n        there is only one code (x00B1) to represent ±. Therefore, both Font1,49 and Font7,93 are\n        mapped to Unicode x00B1 internally inside Uniface. When x00B1 is mapped back to the meta\n        character set, x00B1 can be only mapped to one code and Uniface chooses to map it to\n        Font1,49. It can be undesirable to have Font1,49 returned instead of Font7,93.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__section_kfl_lpb_rcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d713055e192\">Compatibility Assignment Settings</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__p_d28340e1_d28341e1_d28342e1\">Uniface provides the following assignment section and\n        settings to solve these issues.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__note_y4b_npb_rcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The Uniface implementation of Traditional Chinese\n        character set doesn't involve the meta character set. The following settings are not\n        applicable for Traditional Chinese character set.</div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Assignment Section and Settings for Unicode Limitations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__1\">Section/Setting </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gzx1665702657590.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gzx1665702657590.html\" title=\"Use the [META_CharSet ] section of the assignment file to map characters in the Uniface meta character set, for example [META_Japanese] or [META_Western], to and from Unicode.\">[META_CharSet]</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__2\">Specify your own mappings between the meta character\n                set and Unicode. <ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__ul_fpb_npb_rcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14504e1_d14505e1_d14506e1\">If an old application contains the meta\n                    characters that are missing in Unicode, map them to Unicode code points that are\n                    not used in the application. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14507e1_d14508e1_d14509e1\">If characters in an installable character\n                    set are missing in Unicode, use this section to make your own mappings. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14510e1_d14511e1_d14512e1\">If characters in an installable character\n                    set are duplicated in the meta character set and Uniface's default mapping\n                    results in error in the installable character set, such as the ± symbol, define\n                    your own mappings. </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xtc1665702555471.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xtc1665702555471.html\" title=\"Specify which characters are allowed as extended characters (~&amp; or ~@) in the field syntax definition.\">$EXTENDED_SYNTAX</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__2\">For the extended characters (~&amp; or ~@) in the\n                field syntax definition. <ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__ul_kpb_npb_rcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14513e1_d14514e1_d14515e1\">If the database only supports Unicode BMP,\n                    set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$EXTENDED_SYNTAX</span>=<code class=\"ph codeph\">BMP</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14516e1_d14517e1_d14518e1\">If your application contains the meta\n                    characters that are missing in Unicode, set\n                      <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$EXTENDED_SYNTAX</span>=<code class=\"ph codeph\">v8</code>. </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iub1665702713124.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iub1665702713124.html\" title=\"Specify the allowed character set for the field syntax definition, when the full character range is specified (FUL shorthand code).\">$FULL_SYNTAX</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vmy1665702874862__table_d2924e1_d2925e1_d2926e1__entry__2\">For the <code class=\"ph codeph\">FUL</code> shorthand code for field\n                syntax. <ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__ul_qpb_npb_rcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14519e1_d14520e1_d14521e1\">If the database only supports Unicode BMP,\n                    set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$FULL_SYNTAX</span>=<code class=\"ph codeph\">BMP</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vmy1665702874862__li_d14522e1_d14523e1_d14524e1\">If your application contains the meta\n                    characters that are missing in Unicode, set\n                      <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$FULL_SYNTAX</span>=<code class=\"ph codeph\">v8</code>. </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n<div class=\"fn\"><a href=\"#fnsrc_1\" name=\"fntarg_1\"><sup>1</sup></a>  The glyph (and meaning) of Font7.^046 is a\n                  bottle. There is no such glyph in Unicode so Uniface uses Unicode U+2615 (Hot\n                  Beverage) as an internal code, but the representation is different.</div></article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533092\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533092\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Unicode Compatibility Issues Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Unicode Compatibility Issues Earlier versions of Uniface used the Uniface meta character set as its internal character set. Uniface 9 uses Unicode as its internal character set. For compatibility reasons, the meta character set is still used, but this results in some problems. Assignment settings are available to solve these issues. Missing Characters in Unicode Some characters exist in meta character sets but not in Unicode. Table 1. Uniface Meta Characters Missing in Unicode Meta Character Code Description Font2,46 Superscript right arrow Font2,47 Superscript slash Font2,58 Superscript infinity Font2,59 Superscript pi Font2,60 Superscript left angle Font2,62 Superscript right angle Font2,63 Superscript delta Font3,93 Greenlandic capital K Font7,46 Bottle 1 Characters in Font 0, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 7 are shared for all the installable character sets. For more information, see Meta Character Sets . Incorrectly Returned Mappings Some characters have two entry points in the meta character set. For example, symbol ± appears in Font1,49 and Font7,93. However, in Unicode, there is only one code (x00B1) to represent ±. Therefore, both Font1,49 and Font7,93 are mapped to Unicode x00B1 internally inside Uniface. When x00B1 is mapped back to the meta character set, x00B1 can be only mapped to one code and Uniface chooses to map it to Font1,49. It can be undesirable to have Font1,49 returned instead of Font7,93. Compatibility Assignment Settings Uniface provides the following assignment section and settings to solve these issues. Note: The Uniface implementation of Traditional Chinese character set doesn't involve the meta character set. The following settings are not applicable for Traditional Chinese character set. Table 2. Assignment Section and Settings for Unicode Limitations Section/Setting Description [META_CharSet] Specify your own mappings between the meta character set and Unicode. If an old application contains the meta characters that are missing in Unicode, map them to Unicode code points that are not used in the application. If characters in an installable character set are missing in Unicode, use this section to make your own mappings. If characters in an installable character set are duplicated in the meta character set and Uniface's default mapping results in error in the installable character set, such as the ± symbol, define your own mappings. $EXTENDED_SYNTAX For the extended characters (~& or ~@) in the field syntax definition. If the database only supports Unicode BMP, set $EXTENDED_SYNTAX = BMP . If your application contains the meta characters that are missing in Unicode, set $EXTENDED_SYNTAX = v8 . $FULL_SYNTAX For the FUL shorthand code for field syntax. If the database only supports Unicode BMP, set $FULL_SYNTAX = BMP . If your application contains the meta characters that are missing in Unicode, set $FULL_SYNTAX = v8 . 1 The glyph (and meaning) of Font7.^046 is a bottle. There is no such glyph in Unicode so Uniface uses Unicode U+2615 (Hot Beverage) as an internal code, but the representation is different. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}